Posts</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sparkol.com/en/Blog/8-Classic-storytelling-techniques-for-engaging-presentations\">8 Classic Storytelling Techniques for Engaging Presentations</a> - by <strong>Ffion Lindsay</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eleganthack.com/block-your-talk/\">Block Your Talk</a> - by <strong>Christina Wodtke</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.samjarman.co.nz/blog/speaking-gigs\">How To Get Speaking Engagements</a> - by <strong>Sam Jarman</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/public-speaking-tips\">Nine Secrets to Powerful Public Speaking</a> - by <strong>Julian Treasure</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eleganthack.com/presenting-is-performance/\">Presenting is Performance</a> - by <strong>Christina Wodtke</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.troyhunt.com/2015/06/speaker-style-bingo-10-presentation.html\">Speaker Style Bingo: 10 Presentation Anti-Patterns</a> - by <strong>Troy Hunt</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://derickbailey.com/2015/11/11/some-thoughts-on-doing-conference-sessions/\">Some Thoughts On Doing Conference Sessions</a> - by <strong>Derick Bailey</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://wunder.schoenaberselten.com/2016/02/16/how-to-prepare-and-write-a-tech-conference-talk/\">How To Prepare And Write A Tech Conference Talk</a> - by <strong>Lena Reinhard</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920027096.do\">Propose, Prepare, Present</a> - Free Ebook by <strong>Alistair Croll</strong> (O'Reilly)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://presentationpatterns.com/\">Presentation Patterns</a> - by <strong>Neal Ford</strong>, <strong>Matthew McCullough</strong>, and <strong>Nate Schutta</strong> (Addison-Wesley)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0321668790\">Presentation Zen Design</a> - by Garr Reynolds. How to design your presentation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/d/0544634497/\">TED Talks: The Official TED Guide to Public Speaking</a> - by <strong>Chris Anderson</strong> (Houghton Mifflin Harcourt). Start to finish guide to giving powerful talks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"cfp\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cfp\" aria-label=\"cfp permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CFP</h2>\n<p><em>List of Call of Paper sites and services.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.callbackwomen.com/\">Callback Women</a> - Sharing CFPs via <a href=\"https://twitter.com/callbackwomen\">Twitter</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://papercall.io/\">PaperCall</a> - Place to manage your talks and submissions.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/softwaremill/it-cfp-list\">IT CFP List</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/softwaremill/it-cfp-list\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">375</span></span></a> - List of IT conferences Call For Papers, changes are also published via Twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ItCfpList\">@ItCfpList</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://tulu.la\">Tulu.la</a> - Curated list of tech events and open CFPs. Friendly community and speaker support champions. Community-driven.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"clubsorganizations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#clubsorganizations\" aria-label=\"clubsorganizations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Clubs/Organizations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.toastmasters.org/Find-a-Club\">Toastmasters</a> - An international non-profit educational organizations that facilitates the creation and growth of clubs around the world. The goal of the clubs is to improve the leadership and public speaking skills of members.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"miscellaneous\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#miscellaneous\" aria-label=\"miscellaneous permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.